column6: Well this is irritating. Usually when the end of the question is several hours/days/months before the answer would be known, they're explicit about the delay. I was 100% for a 70-80k closing price (currently at 70,074) but it's trending down fairly strongly. Going to make a last minute switch and hope for the best.
Looks like a bullish correction may be afoot.
Reducing <70k bin even though the price fell today, because the market looks oversold from a technical perspective and because today's candlestick chart is hinting at a temporary bottom.
Am probably wrong on this >80k target by June 22nd, so shaving 10% off. Might regret it if I'm right though. Pick and stick mate!
Oversold under 76k, maybe buying back in moves it over 80k again.
This is going to flatten out for maybe a week then start back up hill, but it may not get to 80k again by the 22nd.
Is this sudden downturn a result of uneasiness in Italy as they try to form a government?
WoC0.58 could end up at 79k again. So close but going to just stick with 0.99 on 80k-90k for those sweet points.

Since the index is right in the middle of the 80-90 range at the moment that is the most likely where it is going to end up with some probability of moving away from this range, skewed to the downside.

Brazil is in negotiations with the US about steel export rates. Rising credit interests at the US may force capital withdrawal from Bazil. In October 2018 general elections and presidential elections will be held at Brazil.
